.CM files store collision model data. Collision models are a [binary
space
partitioning](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_space_partitioning "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_space_partitioning")
based format used for collision detection.

They are most commonly used with maps but can also be used with moveable
physics objects.

